00:29:40.597 --> 00:29:41.017
Let's pray.

00:29:41.418 --> 00:29:45.883
Dear God, thank you for this Thanksgiving season, a wonderful chance for us to praise you.

00:29:46.344 --> 00:29:53.293
Even though it seemed like it might not be a great year, tough things, we know we always have things to praise you for and thank you for.

00:29:53.333 --> 00:30:01.684
This leper gave us a great example of how he was able to loudly praise, glorify, and honor Jesus for what he had did.

00:30:02.124 --> 00:30:03.406
Can we do the same?

00:30:03.967 --> 00:30:06.610
Can we act in the same way, God?

00:30:07.426 --> 00:30:08.087
I hope so.

00:30:08.547 --> 00:30:12.612
I hope next week, we break that record that we had last year.

00:30:12.672 --> 00:30:17.799
You know, that's another thing I forgot to mention that last year, because of the pandemic, we've had more testimony than ever.

00:30:18.159 --> 00:30:19.841
Can we have even more this year?

00:30:20.242 --> 00:30:21.243
I sure hope so.

00:30:21.503 --> 00:30:22.364
I sure hope so.

00:30:22.885 --> 00:30:24.767
God, thank you for watching over us.

00:30:24.807 --> 00:30:25.688
Thank you for being with us.

00:30:25.748 --> 00:30:28.572
I speak and please be with everyone the rest of this week.

00:30:29.072 --> 00:30:31.395
And I hope everyone has a happy Thanksgiving.

00:30:31.455 --> 00:30:32.957
We pray all these things in Jesus' name.

00:30:33.398 --> 00:30:33.778
Amen.
